                <li>From the plank, jump both feet forward and lift your hips high into a pike position. Your body should form an inverted V.</li>
                <li>Jump back to the plank position. That's one rep.</li>
              </ol>
              <div class="exercise-card__tip">
                <p><strong>Pro Tip:</strong> Keep your core braced throughout. The goal is to control the movement, not just rush through it.</p>
